WEBVTT

00:01.740 --> 00:04.700
♪♪

00:04.743 --> 00:07.311
I worked with your mother
for 30 years.

00:07.355 --> 00:08.834
We were like family.

00:08.878 --> 00:12.316
Youburned the bridges,
not us.

00:12.360 --> 00:15.319
[ Laughs ] What's up, bro?
What's up?

00:15.363 --> 00:17.713
-You guys are too loud.
-You kidding me, dude?

00:18.714 --> 00:21.021
Deran: If I see either of you
in Oceanside again,

00:21.064 --> 00:22.674
we're gonna have
some real issues, alright?

00:22.718 --> 00:25.329
It's good to have somebody
looking out for us locals again.

00:25.373 --> 00:28.158
-Got clean six years ago.
-Yeah, man, I just got clean,
too.

00:28.202 --> 00:30.856
Only been a few months, though,
but that shit's hard, man.

00:30.900 --> 00:33.163
Hey, hang out with me today.
I need to find a job.

00:33.207 --> 00:36.340
I can't. I got to go meet
some lawyer Smurf found.

00:36.384 --> 00:37.907
Man, can you
believe Smurf?

00:37.950 --> 00:40.344
Andrew's got 60 hours
of community service.

00:40.388 --> 00:41.867
Hey, it's better
than juvie.

00:41.911 --> 00:43.173
Whatever.

00:43.217 --> 00:44.696
I'm worried about Pope.

00:44.740 --> 00:47.177
What's he need 18 grand
worth of lumber for?

00:47.221 --> 00:48.874
No idea.

00:48.918 --> 00:52.530
I spoke to
your vice principal.

00:52.574 --> 00:54.880
-And?
-You're getting expelled.

00:54.924 --> 00:56.360
What?

00:56.404 --> 01:03.411
♪♪

01:03.454 --> 01:09.112
♪ She stares deeply

01:09.156 --> 01:13.247
♪ Locked inside me

01:13.290 --> 01:16.250
♪ Burnin' brightly

01:19.253 --> 01:24.780
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:24.823 --> 01:28.566
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin

01:28.610 --> 01:32.092
♪ Every night now, they'll win

01:35.617 --> 01:38.098
♪ Come and meet my black hole

01:38.141 --> 01:41.971
♪ Got a big black hole

01:42.014 --> 01:45.757
♪ Got a big black hole

01:45.801 --> 01:49.631
♪ I've got a big black hole

01:49.674 --> 01:53.939
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

01:53.983 --> 01:57.595
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

01:57.639 --> 01:59.641
♪ Got a

02:02.034 --> 02:04.515
[ Sizzling ]

02:25.232 --> 02:28.017
How's community service
going?

02:29.671 --> 02:30.846
It's not so bad.

02:30.889 --> 02:33.849
Really?
It's not so bad?

02:33.892 --> 02:37.157
Aren't you picking up dog shit
and candy wrappers?

02:37.200 --> 02:40.160
Better than juvie.

02:40.203 --> 02:44.338
You don't get caught,
you won't have to do either.

02:44.381 --> 02:46.862
Morning, baby.

02:46.905 --> 02:49.299
More eggs coming up
in a minute.

02:49.343 --> 02:52.346
[ Sighs ] I'm okay. I'll grab
something at the food court.

02:52.389 --> 02:54.522
Job at the mall.

02:54.565 --> 02:56.524
Congratulations.

02:58.352 --> 03:00.484
I want to make
my own money.

03:00.528 --> 03:03.183
-Waste of your talents.
-Yourtalent, not mine.

03:03.226 --> 03:05.837
Ourtalents.

03:05.881 --> 03:07.665
I'm gonna save up
for a car.

03:07.709 --> 03:09.885
-Great.
-Then I can go wherever I want.

03:09.928 --> 03:11.539
You do that.

03:13.367 --> 03:14.672
I think it's good
she's got a job.

03:14.716 --> 03:17.675
Eat your breakfast.

03:17.719 --> 03:20.330
Pope:
Why is the gate unlocked?

03:20.374 --> 03:22.506
-I thought I locked it, man.
-You thought you locked it?

03:22.550 --> 03:23.899
Yeah.

03:25.901 --> 03:27.685
[ Engine shuts off ]

03:27.729 --> 03:33.213
♪♪

03:33.256 --> 03:36.346
-Get out.
-Why? I'm not hurting anyone.

03:36.390 --> 03:43.701
♪♪

03:43.745 --> 03:45.268
-Asshole.
-Get out!

03:45.312 --> 03:47.705
-Hey!
-Get out! You get out!

03:47.749 --> 03:50.230
Get out!

03:51.927 --> 03:54.712
Man:
What's your problem, man?

03:54.756 --> 03:57.237
[ Fence rattles ]

03:57.280 --> 04:00.588
[ Breathing heavily ]

04:01.632 --> 04:04.592
It's a ramp.
They're skaters.

04:06.985 --> 04:09.249
[ Cellphone dings ]

04:09.292 --> 04:10.598
Goddamn it.

04:10.641 --> 04:12.730
Cleaning crew from one of
the buildings on Whaley.

04:12.774 --> 04:14.558
I guess one of the tenants
won't leave.

04:14.602 --> 04:16.430
Why are they texting you?
That's Craig's building.

04:16.473 --> 04:18.258
Craig's not picking up,
I guess.

04:18.301 --> 04:20.782
Didn't he offer everyone
5 grand to move out?

04:20.825 --> 04:23.306
I guess somebody really likes
living in that shithole.

04:23.350 --> 04:25.395
He's good.
Let him in.

04:25.439 --> 04:29.312
♪♪

04:29.356 --> 04:30.966
Take a seat.

04:33.142 --> 04:35.405
So, how did we do?

04:35.449 --> 04:38.103
That was a decent haul.

04:38.147 --> 04:40.105
I got rid of that jewelry
real fast.

04:40.149 --> 04:42.282
Seems like Gia had
some good stuff.

04:42.325 --> 04:44.109
Any pushback?

04:44.153 --> 04:46.416
Mm, not so much pushback.

04:46.460 --> 04:48.592
I'm not gonna be able to
move these rocks, though.

04:48.636 --> 04:49.985
What's wrong with them?

04:50.028 --> 04:51.595
Well, there's nothing wrong
with them.

04:51.639 --> 04:53.293
I mean, they're excellent,
right?

04:53.336 --> 04:54.772
That's your problem.

04:54.816 --> 04:56.296
See, blue diamonds,
I show them to anybody,

04:56.339 --> 04:58.472
they're gonna recognize them.

04:58.515 --> 05:00.300
And then they're gonna know
I'm working with the guys

05:00.343 --> 05:02.954
who hit Gia and then whoever
Gia was fencing for...

05:02.998 --> 05:04.434
Let's just say
he's gonna come looking.

05:04.478 --> 05:05.783
What about
a diamond wholesaler?

05:05.827 --> 05:08.003
Someone up in L.A.
or San Francisco?

05:08.046 --> 05:10.310
-What? A legitimate dealer?
-Yeah.

05:10.353 --> 05:11.615
Come on. All they have to do
is check them

05:11.659 --> 05:13.661
against
the stolen gem database.

05:13.704 --> 05:15.619
Look, once upon a time,
these things belonged

05:15.663 --> 05:17.491
to some upstanding citizen
somewhere, right?

05:17.534 --> 05:19.319
No doubt they reported
them missing.

05:19.362 --> 05:21.451
Okay.

05:21.495 --> 05:25.455
Why don't you guys just...
sit on them for a while.

05:25.499 --> 05:27.631
Or throw them in the ocean.

05:27.675 --> 05:30.155
It's your choice.

05:30.199 --> 05:31.374
Thank you.

05:34.725 --> 05:38.163
[ Sighs ] Are we really gonna
sit on these things?

05:38.207 --> 05:40.383
-No.
-Okay.

05:40.427 --> 05:43.212
[ Cellphone dings ]

05:43.255 --> 05:44.996
Shit.
Alright.

05:45.040 --> 05:46.650
I should probably deal with
this building shit

05:46.694 --> 05:49.479
before the cleaning service
give up and leave.

05:49.523 --> 05:54.179
♪♪

05:54.223 --> 05:58.488
Hi. Welcome. Let us know
if you need anything.

05:58.532 --> 06:02.492
You got any mascara
that won't give me pinkeye?

06:02.536 --> 06:05.887
Oh, we don't
sell mascara.

06:05.930 --> 06:12.197
Oh. Um, then can you just
find me some shoes

06:12.241 --> 06:16.027
that don't look like
a pair of potatoes?

06:16.071 --> 06:22.251
♪♪

06:22.294 --> 06:24.688
This is new.

06:24.732 --> 06:27.212
It's an ink tag.

06:27.256 --> 06:30.564
Try to take it off, and it'll
spill ink all over the clothes.

06:32.087 --> 06:34.394
Why are you here?

06:34.437 --> 06:38.398
♪♪

06:38.441 --> 06:41.705
Seriously, Julia?
This place?

06:41.749 --> 06:43.533
Everyone's nice.

06:43.577 --> 06:46.406
♪♪

06:46.449 --> 06:48.756
Minimum wage.

06:48.799 --> 06:51.759
But I get a 50-cent raise
in three months.

06:53.456 --> 06:56.546
Well, 40 hours a week,
full-time,

06:56.590 --> 07:00.420
take out social security
and taxes...

07:00.463 --> 07:04.467
you might be able to afford
a used Pinto...

07:04.511 --> 07:06.426
in about a year.

07:06.469 --> 07:09.341
I have to start somewhere.
At least I'm working.

07:11.474 --> 07:17.611
Working to save up to buy a car
to drive to work.

07:19.308 --> 07:21.310
It's a death spiral.
-What?

07:21.353 --> 07:23.921
So, everyone is supposed to
be like you?

07:23.965 --> 07:25.923
Never work but somehow
always have tons of money?

07:25.967 --> 07:28.273
Excuse me.
I've always worked.

07:28.317 --> 07:30.928
You know,
when I was your age,

07:30.972 --> 07:34.584
I was selling untaxed vodka
out of the back of a van.

07:34.628 --> 07:38.283
I made 400 bucks
in one afternoon.

07:38.327 --> 07:42.287
You think you'll make that much
in a month working here?

07:42.331 --> 07:49.120
♪♪

07:49.164 --> 07:51.166
Let's go.

07:51.209 --> 07:56.606
♪♪

07:56.650 --> 08:00.784
♪♪

08:00.828 --> 08:03.483
-Oh. Ohh!
-Ooh!

08:03.526 --> 08:06.311
That makes that my money.
-Alright.

08:06.355 --> 08:09.619
-Taking Vince's money, huh?
-Why? Should I be showing him
some mercy?

08:09.663 --> 08:12.796
[ Scoffs ] No.
Make it hurt.

08:12.840 --> 08:14.624
Alright.

08:14.668 --> 08:19.150
♪♪

08:19.194 --> 08:21.805
Well, look, I'm gonna give you
a chance to win back your money.

08:21.849 --> 08:23.328
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

08:23.372 --> 08:26.810
[ Inhales sharply ]
Alright, man. Rack 'em up.

08:26.854 --> 08:29.204
I'm gonna get some
chicken wings.

08:29.247 --> 08:31.380
Alright.

08:31.423 --> 08:33.556
Bring back some club sodas,
too.

08:33.600 --> 08:42.652
♪♪

08:42.696 --> 08:51.661
♪♪

08:51.705 --> 08:53.837
-You Thompson?
-Yeah.

08:53.881 --> 08:56.666
Captain Torrez.
That's your desk right there.

08:56.710 --> 09:04.544
♪♪

09:04.587 --> 09:12.247
♪♪

09:12.290 --> 09:14.728
[ Sighs ]

09:14.771 --> 09:16.599
You like bullshit?

09:17.774 --> 09:20.081
[ Chuckles ]
No, I don't.

09:20.124 --> 09:22.692
Good.
Then no bullshit.

09:22.736 --> 09:25.565
I didn't ask for you to be
assigned to my cold-case unit.

09:25.608 --> 09:28.045
Me, neither.

09:28.089 --> 09:30.265
So, what do you got?

09:32.310 --> 09:34.704
Bartender robbed and shot
before the bar opened.

09:34.748 --> 09:36.750
No one saw it.

09:36.793 --> 09:39.230
Two guys killed
in a drive-by.

09:39.274 --> 09:41.102
Witness said the shooter
drove a black car,

09:41.145 --> 09:44.279
possibly gray,
maybe four doors, maybe two.

09:44.322 --> 09:47.587
Female body found buried
out in the mountains.

09:47.630 --> 09:51.068
Violent COD. Coroner said
she'd been in the ground
a couple of years.

09:51.112 --> 09:53.070
Catherine Belen.

09:53.114 --> 09:54.898
Last known address
was in Oceanside.

09:54.942 --> 09:57.727
Uh-huh. Bunch of known
associates who are scumbags.

09:57.771 --> 10:01.601
♪♪

10:01.644 --> 10:03.254
Okay, this one.

10:03.298 --> 10:06.736
You got one job --
to get me some clearances.

10:06.780 --> 10:08.912
And by the book,
alright?

10:08.956 --> 10:12.437
I don't need the D.A. up my ass
over bad police work.

10:12.481 --> 10:14.483
Clearances.

10:14.526 --> 10:16.616
Got it.

10:18.139 --> 10:19.662
Sir.

10:19.706 --> 10:21.446
Uh-huh.

10:21.490 --> 10:23.318
"Yes, sir."

10:23.361 --> 10:33.371
♪♪

10:37.506 --> 10:39.987
[ Moaning pleasurably ]

10:40.030 --> 10:43.643
♪♪

10:43.686 --> 10:46.646
[ Both breathing heavily ]

10:46.689 --> 10:47.777
Yeah.

10:47.821 --> 10:49.126
[ Chuckles ]

10:49.170 --> 10:51.781
I gotta pee.

10:51.825 --> 10:54.523
I'm gonna eat.

10:56.699 --> 10:58.353
You work this shift
a lot?

10:58.396 --> 11:00.137
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

11:00.181 --> 11:01.704
Come back around.

11:01.748 --> 11:03.575
Yeah, maybe I will.

11:14.717 --> 11:17.677
Had to order wings
my own damn self.

11:17.720 --> 11:22.159
That girl...
it was amazing.

11:22.203 --> 11:24.205
-Who? Gianna?
-Mm. Yeah.

11:24.248 --> 11:25.815
That was -- That's her name?
-Yeah.

11:25.859 --> 11:27.338
-Gianna.
-Great woman.

11:27.382 --> 11:29.340
-She's great.
-Great woman.

11:29.384 --> 11:30.820
-Mm-hmm.
-Great ass.

11:30.864 --> 11:32.692
-Fine ass.
-Great mom.

11:34.084 --> 11:36.173
Wait, you know her
from outside the bar?

11:36.217 --> 11:37.697
Yeah, she's my ex-wife.

11:37.740 --> 11:38.828
What?!

11:38.872 --> 11:40.700
Don't trip, man.

11:40.743 --> 11:42.527
Me and her
are on good terms.

11:42.571 --> 11:44.007
I just think she took
a liking to you

11:44.051 --> 11:46.183
because you
emptied my wallet.

11:46.227 --> 11:47.707
Bro, I just
banged your ex-wife,

11:47.750 --> 11:49.360
and you seriously
don't give a shit?

11:49.404 --> 11:50.840
Ex,man.

11:50.884 --> 11:53.538
Look, she got a life,
I got mine.

11:53.582 --> 11:56.367
I mean, technically,
we co-parent.

11:56.411 --> 11:58.848
She does most
of the "co."

11:58.892 --> 12:02.243
♪♪

12:02.286 --> 12:04.767
[ Grinding ]

12:04.811 --> 12:07.291
[ Grinding stops ]

12:08.771 --> 12:10.381
[ Switch clicks,
whirring stops ]

12:10.425 --> 12:13.863
The trick is making them
symmetrical.

12:13.907 --> 12:16.213
Just take off
as little as possible.

12:16.257 --> 12:18.738
0.15 carats
should do it.

12:18.781 --> 12:21.610
As long as
no one can see it.

12:21.653 --> 12:26.746
One time, your mom brought me
a single sapphire earring.

12:26.789 --> 12:30.097
I broke it down,
sold it as a pair.

12:30.140 --> 12:33.927
Probably only bought her
a day and a half of dope.

12:38.845 --> 12:40.237
Nice stones.

12:40.281 --> 12:43.066
If I had the cash,
I'd buy 'em myself.

12:43.110 --> 12:44.764
Right.

12:44.807 --> 12:48.289
Uh, you might wanna try
Garden Grove.

12:48.332 --> 12:51.074
I thought that was all
mom-and-pop places.

12:51.118 --> 12:52.902
Ah, shit, not anymore.

12:52.946 --> 12:54.599
Those moms and pops
had kids,

12:54.643 --> 12:57.689
and those kids
like high-end stuff.

12:59.126 --> 13:01.476
Ever heard
of Eddie Pham?

13:01.519 --> 13:02.782
No.

13:02.825 --> 13:06.089
Start there.
I bet he'd love these.

13:06.133 --> 13:08.962
Alright.
Thank you.

13:12.313 --> 13:14.315
[ Gear clicks,
engine shuts off ]

13:19.711 --> 13:21.626
[ Drill whirring ]

13:21.670 --> 13:26.109
Ah. This is what
all the lumber was for.

13:26.153 --> 13:27.676
Yeah.

13:27.719 --> 13:30.331
Looks great.

13:31.506 --> 13:34.465
When's it gonna
be done?

13:34.509 --> 13:37.294
I don't know.
What's up?

13:37.338 --> 13:40.689
Got a little favor to ask you.
A little apartment thing.

13:40.732 --> 13:42.865
One of Craig's places.

13:42.909 --> 13:44.649
He's not picking up his phone.
I don't know where he's at.

13:44.693 --> 13:47.827
Think you can help me out?

13:47.870 --> 13:49.306
I'm working.

13:49.350 --> 13:52.875
What, are you --
you on a deadline?

13:52.919 --> 13:56.400
Come on, man. It'll just be
a couple hours max.

13:58.533 --> 14:00.665
I can't do it by myself.
Come on.

14:00.709 --> 14:01.884
Okay.

14:08.717 --> 14:10.588
Don't let anybody
ride this.

14:16.029 --> 14:25.995
♪♪

14:26.039 --> 14:36.005
♪♪

14:36.049 --> 14:46.015
♪♪

14:46.059 --> 14:47.930
[ Door closes ]

14:47.974 --> 14:57.940
♪♪

14:57.984 --> 15:07.950
♪♪

15:07.994 --> 15:15.044
♪♪

15:15.088 --> 15:17.046
Hello.

15:17.090 --> 15:19.614
Can I help you?

15:20.789 --> 15:22.573
The door was unlocked.

15:22.617 --> 15:25.402
Well, we're always open.

15:25.446 --> 15:28.144
What's your name?

15:29.972 --> 15:32.409
I'm a priest,
not a cop.

15:32.453 --> 15:34.759
Andrew.

15:34.803 --> 15:36.936
Hi, Andrew.

15:36.979 --> 15:39.112
I'm Father Kirby.

15:43.333 --> 15:46.597
So, what's the deal
with the nails?

15:46.641 --> 15:49.818
You mean
the crucifixion?

15:49.861 --> 15:52.168
Did they
really do that?

15:54.649 --> 15:59.784
Well, the Romans normally
tied people to the cross,

15:59.828 --> 16:03.963
so the nails
are for more pain.

16:07.009 --> 16:10.273
Yeah.
He died for our sins.

16:10.317 --> 16:12.710
My sins, your sins.

16:15.496 --> 16:19.804
There's a reason
you came through that door.

16:19.848 --> 16:21.676
I mean, come on.

16:21.719 --> 16:25.158
You're not mowing the lawn
of the county for fun.

16:25.201 --> 16:27.812
[ Sighs ]

16:27.856 --> 16:30.467
Do you want to tell me
what happened that got you here?

16:30.511 --> 16:36.299
♪♪

16:36.343 --> 16:42.001
♪♪

16:42.044 --> 16:45.656
Pope: Craig's booting all
the tenants out of this place?

16:45.700 --> 16:48.007
Deran: Yeah,
it was J's idea.

16:48.050 --> 16:50.487
He offered this dickhead money
to move?

16:50.531 --> 16:52.141
Why?

16:52.185 --> 16:54.317
I don't know.
Path of least resistance?

16:54.361 --> 16:57.494
Throw him off the balcony.
No resistance there.

16:57.538 --> 17:00.323
Yeah, no,
we're not doing that.

17:00.367 --> 17:03.065
Did you go by and see
if he was at his gym?

17:03.109 --> 17:04.371
No, he wasn't.

17:07.069 --> 17:09.158
Quinn,
open up, man.

17:09.202 --> 17:10.507
Quinn: Just a minute!

17:10.551 --> 17:12.857
What's the gym like?

17:12.901 --> 17:14.772
Treadmills and shit.

17:16.905 --> 17:19.734
Yo!
Open up, man.

17:21.257 --> 17:23.520
Let's go!

17:23.564 --> 17:25.348
[ Gun cocks ]

17:25.392 --> 17:26.610
Shit!

17:30.788 --> 17:39.232
♪♪

17:39.275 --> 17:41.060
I ain't leaving!

17:41.103 --> 17:43.758
Cops are gonna show up here if
we don't do anything about this.

17:43.801 --> 17:46.065
Let them shoot him.
That'd be an option.

17:46.108 --> 17:47.414
No. They're gonna want to
investigate the shooting,

17:47.457 --> 17:49.111
and then they're gonna
ask questions about

17:49.155 --> 17:50.721
the ownership of the building.
We're not doing that.

17:50.765 --> 17:53.246
I been here 20 years!
Ain't bothered nobody!

17:53.289 --> 17:55.378
Smurf shoulda done background
checks on her goddamn tenants,

17:55.422 --> 17:57.206
I'll tell you that much.
-I ain't leaving!

17:57.250 --> 17:59.121
You're gonna have to
come kill me today!

17:59.165 --> 18:01.776
Come get me!

18:01.819 --> 18:03.386
Come evict me,
son of a bitches!

18:03.430 --> 18:05.214
What are you gonna do?

18:05.258 --> 18:07.086
Count to 10.
Throw this.

18:07.129 --> 18:09.088
-What?
-Seriously. Yeah.

18:09.131 --> 18:10.741
Start now.
-I ain't leaving!

18:10.785 --> 18:13.222
-You serious? Alright.
-Yeah.

18:13.266 --> 18:14.397
I'm gonna go. Ready?
-Okay.

18:14.441 --> 18:15.920
Go.

18:15.964 --> 18:18.967
-I ain't going back!
-10...

18:19.010 --> 18:21.404
-20 years I've been here!
-...9...

18:21.448 --> 18:24.103
Quinn: Me and my ducks!
I ain't done nothing to nobody!

18:24.146 --> 18:25.974
...8...
Goddamn it.

18:26.017 --> 18:28.933
...7...

18:28.977 --> 18:30.935
6...
-I ain't going nowhere!

18:30.979 --> 18:34.809
20 years!
Don't come mess with me today!

18:34.852 --> 18:37.594
♪♪

18:37.638 --> 18:38.943
...1.

18:38.987 --> 18:40.423
Aah!

18:40.467 --> 18:42.773
[ Glass shatters ]

18:42.817 --> 18:44.601
[ Gun cocks ]

18:44.645 --> 18:51.782
♪♪

18:51.826 --> 18:54.133
[ Both grunting ]

18:54.176 --> 18:55.960
Get inside.

18:56.004 --> 18:59.138
Get inside. Come on.
Get inside. Come on.

19:03.707 --> 19:05.013
[ Engine shuts off ]

19:07.189 --> 19:08.843
[ Door opens ]

19:10.845 --> 19:12.629
Not your day.

19:12.673 --> 19:14.022
You got a minute?

19:21.856 --> 19:23.466
What's up, primo?

19:23.510 --> 19:25.294
Abuela.

19:25.338 --> 19:27.862
[ Speaks Spanish ]

19:30.560 --> 19:33.172
Look, can we just
do this over here?

19:33.215 --> 19:36.175
Huh? I mean, how long are you
gonna live here for?

19:36.218 --> 19:38.481
-None of your business.
-Renn, we should be together.

19:38.525 --> 19:40.309
-Oh, don't do this again.
-Look, can we just go talk
about this over here, huh?

19:40.353 --> 19:42.311
-Stop, Craig.
-Look, listen.

19:42.355 --> 19:44.487
I don't want to co-parent.
Okay?

19:44.531 --> 19:46.185
So, why don't you just come home
and parent with me,

19:46.228 --> 19:48.230
and we can figure out --
It's just easier.

19:48.274 --> 19:50.014
-I said no.
-It's gonna be easier
if we try to figure this out.

19:50.058 --> 19:51.842
Come on. Let's go.
-I said no, Craig.

19:51.886 --> 19:53.888
-What's your problem, bro?
-Hey! Hey!

19:53.931 --> 19:55.672
Brandon [speaks Spanish]
Out!

19:55.716 --> 19:57.370
-Let's go.
-I said out!

19:57.413 --> 19:59.894
So, that's it? I get sober for
you, and this is what I get?

19:59.937 --> 20:02.201
-Oh, for me?
-Yeah, for you! And for Nick!

20:02.244 --> 20:04.333
Because someone in this family
needs to pull their shit
together, Renn!

20:04.377 --> 20:05.856
-Your shit together?
-Yeah, you!

20:05.900 --> 20:07.336
You're high now!
-I'm not high!

20:07.380 --> 20:09.512
High or sober,
you're still being an asshole!

20:09.556 --> 20:11.079
[ Door slams ]

20:11.122 --> 20:13.255
Renn, I'm still getting my day
next week with Nick!

20:13.299 --> 20:15.910
Do you hear me?

20:15.953 --> 20:18.086
Goddamn it.

20:18.129 --> 20:27.356
♪♪

20:27.400 --> 20:29.358
Shiny, shiny.

20:29.402 --> 20:36.060
♪♪

20:36.104 --> 20:37.888
Three grand.

20:37.932 --> 20:40.239
They're worth
way more than that.

20:40.282 --> 20:42.545
[ Speaks Vietnamese ]

20:42.589 --> 20:45.940
Hey.
[ Speaks Vietnamese ]

20:45.983 --> 20:49.726
♪♪

20:49.770 --> 20:51.728
[ Speaks Vietnamese ]

20:51.772 --> 20:56.080
♪♪

20:56.124 --> 21:00.259
Here's the problem.
Those diamonds are nice.

21:00.302 --> 21:05.089
Like, uh, color
and clarity's top grade.

21:05.133 --> 21:08.745
Um...I inherited them
from my grandmother.

21:08.789 --> 21:10.399
Oh, from Grandma?

21:10.443 --> 21:12.749
-Yeah.
-Okay.

21:12.793 --> 21:14.403
I hope that's true,

21:14.447 --> 21:16.971
'cause if there's anything off
with these rocks,

21:17.014 --> 21:20.279
this gnome right here,
he gonna catch it.

21:22.150 --> 21:24.805
He's the best gemologist
there is, bar none.

21:26.981 --> 21:28.809
Nguoi lun!

21:28.852 --> 21:33.292
♪♪

21:33.335 --> 21:37.165
Look, if you're not interested,
I can go. I swear, no problem.

21:39.472 --> 21:41.778
They're good.

21:41.822 --> 21:46.000
♪♪

21:46.043 --> 21:48.785
Well, if the troll says
they're good, then they're good.

21:48.829 --> 21:53.137
♪♪

21:53.181 --> 21:55.618
Eighty.

21:55.662 --> 21:58.186
That's great.

21:58.229 --> 21:59.840
The hell was that shit,
man?

21:59.883 --> 22:01.972
You pull a shotgun
for this place?!

22:02.016 --> 22:03.800
It's my home.

22:03.844 --> 22:06.455
Yeah, well,
not anymore.

22:06.499 --> 22:10.329
20 years.
My place.

22:10.372 --> 22:12.331
Me and my ducks.

22:18.206 --> 22:20.164
Smurf gave me this place.

22:20.208 --> 22:21.818
She said, "Kill the rats."

22:21.862 --> 22:25.474
Y-You know how many rats
I done killed for Smurf? Huh?

22:25.518 --> 22:27.346
Hey, you can get a cat
to do the same shit.

22:27.389 --> 22:29.652
I kept my mouth shut
to stuff I saw.

22:29.696 --> 22:32.176
Y-Your mom even knew that.
-Yeah, well, it doesn't
matter now,

22:32.220 --> 22:33.656
'cause you got to get
the hell out of here, okay?

22:33.700 --> 22:35.005
I don't know what to tell you.
I'm sorry.

22:35.049 --> 22:37.225
You gotta pack your shit up
and go.

22:37.268 --> 22:39.532
Quinn: I was in Afghanistan
only 48 hours

22:39.575 --> 22:41.838
when an IED
messed up my head.

22:41.882 --> 22:44.058
VA didn't do shit.

22:44.101 --> 22:46.669
But Smurf
gave me this place.

22:46.713 --> 22:48.715
-I'm not asking, man.
-You got my gun.

22:48.758 --> 22:51.370
Kill me.
You kill me.

22:51.413 --> 22:56.026
I slept on the beach, on
the street, behind a dumpster.

22:56.070 --> 22:58.246
I ain't going back.

22:58.289 --> 23:00.379
I ain't going back!

23:06.907 --> 23:09.388
If we put this guy out,
he's gonna be dead in a week.

23:09.431 --> 23:12.042
Okay, but he put a 12-gauge
on both of us.

23:12.086 --> 23:13.435
You wanna play
Salvation Army now?

23:13.479 --> 23:16.220
Shit gets complicated, Deran.
You know that.

23:16.264 --> 23:20.224
Smurf took this guy in.
Smurf ain't here.

23:20.268 --> 23:23.314
What's he supposed to do?

23:26.622 --> 23:29.059
Uh...

23:29.103 --> 23:32.106
Alright, listen.

23:32.149 --> 23:36.415
Pack your shit,
take your ducks and shit.

23:36.458 --> 23:39.156
I think I know a place
where you can stay, alright?

23:49.340 --> 23:52.082
You are
wasting your time.

23:52.126 --> 23:54.258
We already know who killed
Catherine Belen.

23:54.302 --> 23:56.130
-Hmm?
-Baby-daddy.

23:56.173 --> 23:57.740
Baz Blackwell.

23:57.784 --> 23:59.307
So, why isn't
the case closed?

23:59.350 --> 24:01.962
Well, 'cause he's dead, too.
What are you gonna do?

24:02.005 --> 24:03.920
What if it wasn't
Blackwell?

24:03.964 --> 24:06.270
What if the guy that buried her
is still walking around?

24:06.314 --> 24:08.577
Uh, well,
we've worked it.

24:08.621 --> 24:11.972
Yeah. I keep seeing the names
"Pierce" and "Chadwick."

24:12.015 --> 24:14.104
Where are they?

24:14.148 --> 24:16.759
Pierce retired,
Chadwick moved East.

24:16.803 --> 24:19.458
The Codys tend to have
that effect on people.

24:19.501 --> 24:21.938
The Codys.

24:21.982 --> 24:25.638
Right. Andrew, Craig,
Deran, and --

24:25.681 --> 24:27.944
Joshua -- J --
their nephew.

24:27.988 --> 24:30.469
And Andrew
goes by Pope.

24:30.512 --> 24:32.122
-Why?
-Who the hell knows?

24:32.166 --> 24:33.776
Not because
he went to seminary.

24:33.820 --> 24:35.952
Hey,
get the Cody files.

24:35.996 --> 24:37.606
I need to see everything
you have on them.

24:37.650 --> 24:39.652
On its way.

24:41.697 --> 24:43.960
Wait, Catherine Belen
was a criminal informant?

24:44.004 --> 24:46.354
Yeah, against Blackwell.
That's why we know he did it.

24:48.182 --> 24:51.490
A C.I. dies, and Oceanside P.D.
lets the case go cold?

24:51.533 --> 24:54.623
Again, Baz Blackwell
is extremely dead.

24:54.667 --> 24:56.146
And who killed him?

24:56.190 --> 24:59.367
Probably his mother.
She's dead, too.

25:00.716 --> 25:02.675
"Probably."

25:02.718 --> 25:04.546
Cody files.

25:04.590 --> 25:06.983
Ooh.
[ Exhales deeply ]

25:07.027 --> 25:08.985
Have fun.

25:09.029 --> 25:16.558
♪♪

25:16.602 --> 25:24.174
♪♪

25:24.218 --> 25:25.654
Have a nice day.

25:25.698 --> 25:28.352
Hey.
Don't come back.

25:28.396 --> 25:33.749
♪♪

25:46.936 --> 25:48.851
[ Gear clicks ]

25:48.895 --> 25:51.027
[ Engine shuts off ]

25:51.071 --> 25:53.377
What's this?

25:53.421 --> 25:55.728
Told you I'd find
a spot for you.

26:00.602 --> 26:03.213
-Oh. Hey, man.
-Hey.

26:03.257 --> 26:06.608
-How's the new board
working out for you?
-Oh, it's great. Thanks.

26:06.652 --> 26:09.568
Hey, uh, you still got
that spare room in the back?

26:09.611 --> 26:12.614
Yeah, sure. I just, uh --
I use it for storage.

26:12.658 --> 26:15.748
Well, I got somebody
that needs it.

26:24.104 --> 26:26.976
He'll help you
clear it out.

26:31.677 --> 26:33.940
What's wrong with him?

26:33.983 --> 26:36.290
Nothing.
He just needs a place to stay.

26:46.126 --> 26:49.608
Why are we here?
I have to go back.

26:49.651 --> 26:52.480
Drink your milkshake.

26:53.786 --> 26:55.744
I'm gonna get fired.

26:55.788 --> 26:57.616
[ Chuckles ]

26:57.659 --> 27:00.096
Jobs like that
don't fire people.

27:00.140 --> 27:02.621
[ Vehicle approaches ]

27:09.149 --> 27:11.281
Do you know him?

27:11.325 --> 27:12.631
He's a...

27:12.674 --> 27:14.284
[ Car door closes ]

27:14.328 --> 27:16.286
...car broker.

27:16.330 --> 27:18.462
[ Scoffs ] Car broker.
Right.

27:18.506 --> 27:20.987
You wanna take it
for a spin?

27:23.511 --> 27:26.122
-Really?
-Yeah.

27:26.166 --> 27:29.299
I mean, you wanna buy a car,
right?

27:29.343 --> 27:31.519
So...

27:33.695 --> 27:36.655
Aren't you gonna do
any research?

27:43.531 --> 27:44.967
Okay, Grandma.

27:45.011 --> 27:47.187
Come on.
Give it some juice.

27:47.230 --> 27:49.711
[ Engine revving ]

27:49.755 --> 27:51.800
♪♪

27:51.844 --> 27:53.497
[ Tires screech ]

27:53.541 --> 27:54.803
Ahh!

27:54.847 --> 28:01.810
♪♪

28:01.854 --> 28:03.333
[ Tires screech ]

28:03.377 --> 28:07.381
Oh, you got it, baby.
You got it!

28:07.424 --> 28:08.991
[ Tires screech ]

28:09.035 --> 28:10.210
[ Horn blares ]

28:10.253 --> 28:12.342
[ Tires screech ]

28:12.386 --> 28:15.563
[ Tires squealing ]

28:15.606 --> 28:18.348
Jesus!
You almost killed me!

28:18.392 --> 28:20.699
Get a haircut.

28:20.742 --> 28:23.005
[ Laughs ]

28:23.049 --> 28:25.834
[ Engine revving ]

28:25.878 --> 28:35.539
♪♪

28:35.583 --> 28:37.846
[ Tires screech ]

28:37.890 --> 28:40.370
[ Both laugh ]

28:40.414 --> 28:43.069
[ Laughing ]
Oh, my God!

28:44.766 --> 28:47.073
That's my girl.

28:47.116 --> 28:49.728
Do you like it?
Does it get your approval?

28:49.771 --> 28:51.599
Are you kidding?

28:54.428 --> 28:57.039
Very much so. This --
I can't even --

28:57.083 --> 28:59.563
This car's amazing.

28:59.607 --> 29:01.914
You want it?

29:04.481 --> 29:06.440
You're messing
with me.

29:06.483 --> 29:08.268
No.

29:10.096 --> 29:12.054
Wait, seriously?

29:12.098 --> 29:13.229
[ Car door closes ]

29:13.273 --> 29:15.754
You want it,
it's yours.

29:17.799 --> 29:19.801
Yes!
Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes!

29:19.845 --> 29:21.934
Thank you so much!

29:21.977 --> 29:24.240
It's my pleasure.

29:24.284 --> 29:27.243
There's one thing.

29:27.287 --> 29:32.945
This car
is 110% stolen.

29:32.988 --> 29:39.908
♪♪

29:39.952 --> 29:42.955
-I don't know, Smurf.
-Oh, cut the shit, baby.

29:44.478 --> 29:47.263
You knew this car was hot
as soon as it pulled up,

29:47.307 --> 29:49.309
and you still got in.

29:52.660 --> 29:55.619
I don't have time
for an ethics debate.

29:55.663 --> 30:00.842
You could be cruising with your
friends down the strand tonight.

30:03.540 --> 30:08.284
Or I can drop you off
back at your...

30:08.328 --> 30:10.460
mall job.

30:10.504 --> 30:16.815
♪♪

30:16.858 --> 30:18.817
Thanks.

30:18.860 --> 30:21.645
[ Indistinct talking
on television ]

30:21.689 --> 30:23.125
[ Clears throat ]

30:23.169 --> 30:26.650
Well, the dedicated gym owner
arrives.

30:26.694 --> 30:29.218
Not in the mood.

30:31.220 --> 30:33.353
There you go.

30:35.181 --> 30:37.705
Get you a Shirley Temple, too,
if you want.

30:40.012 --> 30:42.971
Hey.
Diamonds sold.

30:43.015 --> 30:44.190
Nice.

30:44.233 --> 30:46.148
Maybe we should
hit Gia again.

30:46.192 --> 30:48.150
There's something bigger.

30:48.194 --> 30:49.673
This diamond guy,

30:49.717 --> 30:51.850
he boasted the whole time
about his famous clients.

30:51.893 --> 30:53.982
Paid 80 grand for those,
just like that.

30:54.026 --> 30:56.158
-Whoa.
-So he's just sitting on cash?

30:56.202 --> 30:59.161
I don't know, but he doesn't
just sell jewelry.

30:59.205 --> 31:01.163
He makes it, too.
A lot of it.

31:01.207 --> 31:02.686
On-site?

31:02.730 --> 31:04.384
Mm-hmm.

31:04.427 --> 31:06.342
Pulled pork.

31:06.386 --> 31:08.344
LeRon down the street
made it.

31:08.388 --> 31:11.870
The red sauce is sweet,
orange sauce is hot.

31:11.913 --> 31:13.523
Thanks, Tommy.

31:13.567 --> 31:23.533
♪♪

31:23.577 --> 31:27.015
You got a problem?

31:27.059 --> 31:29.365
Tommy.

31:29.409 --> 31:32.891
Another one.

31:32.934 --> 31:35.415
Get this man a beer.

31:37.460 --> 31:40.594
[ Urinating ]

31:40.637 --> 31:43.945
[ Sighs ]

31:45.425 --> 31:48.210
Stopped by the gym
this morning.

31:48.254 --> 31:51.039
Can I at least
take a piss?

31:51.083 --> 31:53.433
I heard you got a new friend --
Vince.

31:53.476 --> 31:55.565
[ Scoffs, sniffs ]

31:55.609 --> 31:58.612
'Cause, uh, you know, while you
and Vince were hanging out,

31:58.655 --> 32:01.920
me and Pope were nearly
getting our heads blown off

32:01.963 --> 32:04.574
taking care
of your shit.

32:04.618 --> 32:05.924
What shit?

32:05.967 --> 32:07.229
[ Water running ]

32:07.273 --> 32:08.752
The building on Whaley,
man.

32:08.796 --> 32:10.972
It was supposed to
be empty.

32:14.280 --> 32:15.759
Whoops.

32:15.803 --> 32:22.070
♪♪

32:22.114 --> 32:25.073
[ Bottle thuds ]

32:25.117 --> 32:28.468
[ Both laughing ]

32:30.339 --> 32:33.429
Oh, my God.
It felt like --

32:33.473 --> 32:36.258
It felt like
we were just floating.

32:36.302 --> 32:38.608
She really thought
that you were gonna kill her.

32:38.652 --> 32:40.828
-I thought so, too!
-Really.

32:40.871 --> 32:43.309
[ Laughing ]

32:43.352 --> 32:46.790
[ Radio playing ]

32:46.834 --> 32:51.143
You know,
the funny thing is...

32:51.186 --> 32:59.107
♪♪

32:59.151 --> 33:03.633
...it's -- it's actually
really hard to kill a person.

33:03.677 --> 33:07.463
♪ I'm too much with myself,
I wanna be... ♪

33:07.507 --> 33:11.293
But it is really easy

33:11.337 --> 33:13.643
to make someone think
that you're gonna kill them.

33:13.687 --> 33:16.342
♪ I wanna be someone else

33:16.385 --> 33:18.997
♪ I'm too much with myself

33:19.040 --> 33:21.825
[ Both laughing ]

33:21.869 --> 33:26.482
♪ So we take off
out Fiona's door ♪

33:26.526 --> 33:29.137
♪ Walk until it's light
outside ♪

33:29.181 --> 33:30.704
Hey, baby.

33:30.747 --> 33:33.489
♪ Like before
when we were on the phone ♪

33:33.533 --> 33:35.317
You forgot to pick me up.

33:35.361 --> 33:38.668
Oh.
I'm sorry, baby.

33:38.712 --> 33:40.888
I'm sorry.

33:42.194 --> 33:44.848
How'd you get home?

33:44.892 --> 33:47.503
Father Kirby
dropped me off.

33:47.547 --> 33:49.853
[ Chuckles ] Who?

33:49.897 --> 33:51.551
Father --
[ Laughs ]

33:51.594 --> 33:52.856
[ Laughing ]

33:52.900 --> 33:54.858
Father -- Fa--
Father Kirby?

33:54.902 --> 33:56.860
[ Both laughing ]

33:56.904 --> 33:59.385
[ Laughing ]
Father Kirby.

33:59.428 --> 34:01.039
-Oh.
-You're awesome.

34:01.082 --> 34:02.344
Aww.

34:02.388 --> 34:06.348
Andrew! Andrew!

34:06.392 --> 34:08.524
♪♪

34:08.568 --> 34:11.179
Hey. Hey.

34:11.223 --> 34:13.877
Hey. Hey. Andrew!

34:13.921 --> 34:16.619
Andrew:
Leave me alone.

34:21.407 --> 34:23.713
I'm sorry
we forgot you.

34:23.757 --> 34:25.454
It doesn't matter.

34:29.241 --> 34:31.373
I can pick you up
from now on.

34:31.417 --> 34:33.549
You have a car?

34:33.593 --> 34:36.378
Yeah.
Red one in the driveway.

34:36.422 --> 34:39.207
Kinda hard to miss.
[ Laughs ]

34:39.251 --> 34:41.383
That's yours?

34:41.427 --> 34:43.559
Ours.

34:43.603 --> 34:46.606
♪♪

34:46.649 --> 34:49.609
I can drive you
wherever you want.

34:49.652 --> 34:52.090
From Smurf.

34:52.133 --> 34:57.791
♪♪

34:57.834 --> 34:59.097
[ Sighs ]

34:59.140 --> 35:01.751
You're such a buzzkill.

35:01.795 --> 35:10.760
♪♪

35:10.804 --> 35:13.763
Come on.
Don't be holier-than-thou.

35:13.807 --> 35:17.593
♪♪

35:17.637 --> 35:20.814
Smurf's a bitch, but at least
I got a car out of it.

35:22.990 --> 35:24.252
Good for you.

35:24.296 --> 35:33.131
♪♪

35:33.174 --> 35:35.611
[ Door opens ]

35:35.655 --> 35:37.657
[ Door closes ]

35:41.182 --> 35:48.146
♪♪

35:48.189 --> 35:49.973
What's up, man?
You seen Vince?

35:50.017 --> 35:51.279
In the back.

35:51.323 --> 35:52.672
Yeah?

35:52.715 --> 35:59.983
♪♪

36:00.027 --> 36:01.637
There he is.

36:01.681 --> 36:04.162
What's going on, man?

36:13.519 --> 36:16.696
Those are some red eyes,
bro.

36:16.739 --> 36:19.002
[ Inhales sharply,
clicks tongue ]

36:19.046 --> 36:21.527
Yeah, I messed up, man.

36:24.225 --> 36:26.009
Busted my ass
to stay clean,

36:26.053 --> 36:30.318
and I just pissed it away
in 10 minutes.

36:30.362 --> 36:38.370
♪♪

36:38.413 --> 36:41.242
Yeah, it's not
a straight path.

36:41.286 --> 36:43.070
No.

36:43.113 --> 36:46.334
People like me
drunk and high.

36:46.378 --> 36:49.946
My ex, my brothers.

36:51.905 --> 36:54.081
It started
with my mom.

36:55.604 --> 36:56.866
[ Sighs ]

36:56.910 --> 36:59.217
Hey.

36:59.260 --> 37:01.741
I got what you need.

37:01.784 --> 37:03.699
[ Chuckles ]

37:03.743 --> 37:05.875
It better not
be your ex, man.

37:05.919 --> 37:08.530
